
⚙️ Installation & Usage

1️⃣ Clone the Repository

git clone https://github.com/your-username/log-file-analyzer.git
cd log-file-analyzer

2️⃣ Install Dependencies

Make sure you have Python installed. Then run:

pip install -r requirements.txt

3️⃣ Add Log Files

Place your log files (e.g., test.log) inside the sample_logs/ folder.

4️⃣ Run the Analyzer

Execute the script using:

python log_analyzer.py

5️⃣ View the Results

Suspicious IPs and summary will be shown in the console.

Detailed reports and charts will be saved in the output/ folder

